text:
A 1970 A150K Aerobat cost $12,000 as opposed to the $11,450 price for a 150K Commuter model.
A total of 1101 were built; 875 as the 150K and 226 as the A150K.  Reims also built a total of 210 aircraft; 129 as the F150K and 81 as the FA150K Aerobat.
150L/A150L
Introduced for the 1971 model year with tubular landing gear legs replacing the previous flat steel leaf spring gear.  Also in 1971, the landing and taxi lights were moved from the wing leading edge to the nose bowl to better illuminate the ground.  The 150L also introduced a longer dorsal strake that reached to the rear window.  The 1972 model year the received new fuel filler caps to reduce moisture seepage, and better seats and seat tracks.  1973 brought in lower seats to provide more headroom for taller pilots.
